Given	I'm logged-in with valid credentials
When I select 'Female' radio button from Page 01 of Pelvic MRI
And I select any Examination radio button from Page 01 of Pelvic MRI
Then I go to Page 06 of Pelvic MRI
And I click on 'Finding' radio button
And dropdown below 'Finding' is enabled

When I select 'Endometriosis' from the dropdown
Then 'Add new finding' button is enabled
And 'Characterization I' tab is preselected

When I select 'Characterization II' tab
Then 'T1w signal' slider is enabled
And 'T1w signal FS' slider is enabled
And 'T2w signal' slider is enabled

And 'Multifocal signal increase in the fat-saturated T1w' checkbox is enabled
And 'Multifocal signal increase in the T2w' checkbox is enabled
And 'Cystic' checkbox is enabled
And 'Calcification' checkbox is enabled
And 'Capsule' checkbox is enabled
And 'Septa' checkbox is enabled
And 'Necrosis' checkbox is enabled
And 'Signal voids' checkbox is enabled
And 'Internal bleeding' checkbox is enabled

And 'Possibly superinfected/necrotic areas' checkbox is enabled
And 'Focal signal voids' checkbox is enabled

When I drag 'T1w signal' slider to 'Hyperintense' option
Then it stays at the 'Hyperintense' option

When I drag 'T1w signal FS' slider to 'Hyperintense' option
Then it stays at the 'Hyperintense' option

When I drag 'T2w signal' slider to 'Hyperintense' option
Then 'Homogeneous' radio button is enabled
And 'Heterogeneous' radio button is enabled
And 'Shading' checkbox is enabled

When I select 'Cystic' checkbox
Then 'Complex' checkbox is enabled
And 'Detection of blood clots' checkbox is enabled
